leadership in the legislature and in the 
governor's office remained the same. Jim Lewis

31:38.835 --> 31:40.217
was still speaker. Bill Hobby was the lieutenant 
governor. Grant Jones chaired the Senate Finance

31:45.353 --> 31:53.067
Committee and Jim Rudd was chairman of the House 
Appropriations Committee.

31:55.751 --> 32:07.632
State Representative Tom Muher was still the 
chairman of Budget and Oversight and sat on the

31:55.751 --> 32:07.632
Appropriations Committee representing higher 
education. There were several issues that arose

32:08.692 --> 32:18.422
during the session that were not contemplated 
prior to the session convening. Early in the

32:20.684 --> 32:29.753
session, I was contacted by State Representative 
Eddie Cavazos, who represented the Corpus

32:20.684 --> 32:29.753
Christi area.

